user.description:
I run a blog/art-project called VHSPositive.com, "the unholy magnetic union". As a long time film and science fan, I scour the dark recesses of the internet and ebay searching for great images in bad, bad films, for the most part.

This is a project where I use a variety of hardware and software to recreate the world the way I saw it represented while growing up in the VHS generation. I find images or footage, process them in a variety of ways, then share these with the world. I create a stream of imagery which is a reflection of the world as it looked 40 years ago.

If you like these gifs i create would like to see more goto: VHSPositive.com
If you like the stills I offer prints of some of my work at: 
https://www.etsy.com/shop/VHSPositive
